requirement: The Fault Manager shall transition to an Error state within its Normal state's Error Monitoring region upon receiving an error signal and send a local response request, then return to Error Free when the error is resolved; transition from the Normal state to a Normal-Safe Transition state upon a fault signal and initiate a system response request; from the Normal-Safe Transition state, transition to either the Safe state or back to the Normal state upon system response completion; and transition from the Safe state to the Normal-Safe Transition state upon a recovery signal, then to the Normal state upon subsequent system response completion.
